cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the problem of 3D shape reconstruction from RGB views, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The method proposed involves training a CNN to predict a shape representation from multiple views, which is a machine learning approach (cs.LG) and involves the use of permutation equivariant layers, which is a common technique in deep learning (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also mentions the potential application of the method in robotics (cs.RO) for object recognition and manipulation.
